WEBVTT

02:16.919 --> 02:20.618
People never think about
the cruelty of the Bible,

02:20.662 --> 02:22.751
the violence.

02:25.493 --> 02:28.235
We teach children with hand
puppets and coloring books

02:28.278 --> 02:30.802
some of the bloodiest stories

02:30.846 --> 02:32.456
and then tell them

02:32.500 --> 02:35.590
that it all means
we should love each other.

02:36.243 --> 02:40.116
That's what some
would call a paradox.

02:42.597 --> 02:45.252
What does anyone who's
known that kind of violence

02:45.295 --> 02:47.776
understand about love?

02:52.128 --> 02:55.262
When Samson tied
300 foxes together

02:55.305 --> 02:57.786
and lit them on fire.

03:00.267 --> 03:04.793
Killed a thousand men
with a donkey jawbone.

03:04.836 --> 03:07.012
A thousand.

03:10.929 --> 03:15.020
Pushed a temple over
after his eyes were put out.

03:17.719 --> 03:20.635
'Course Samson
was the lucky one.

03:22.071 --> 03:25.683
In the end, he didn't have to
see the monster he became.

03:32.951 --> 03:35.171
A man can only see
so much darkness

03:35.215 --> 03:37.434
before he goes blind.

05:13.922 --> 05:16.228
Charlie boy!

05:31.374 --> 05:33.376
Who's this?

05:33.420 --> 05:36.684
- Oh, that's Bruce.
- Bruce?

05:39.904 --> 05:43.865
You know, they say food tastes
different on the outside, Bruce.

05:45.127 --> 05:47.172
What you say?

05:48.043 --> 05:49.827
Shit, I don't know.

05:49.871 --> 05:52.177
I try not to eat prison food
on the outside.

05:57.705 --> 05:58.967
Let's get the fuck out of here.

06:10.370 --> 06:11.936
Hey, Tara.

06:13.111 --> 06:14.025
Brad.

06:15.462 --> 06:18.029
What are you --
a produce manager now?

06:18.073 --> 06:20.684
I'm a whatever-needs-to-get-
done-around-here manager.

06:20.728 --> 06:21.990
Fruit ain't gonna stock itself.

06:22.033 --> 06:23.644
Oh, I hear that.

06:24.471 --> 06:28.344
So, did you hear
about Morgan's baby?

06:29.127 --> 06:31.478
We got a call she wanted
to deliver at home.

06:31.521 --> 06:34.176
Kid started coming out,
but it was breeched.

06:34.219 --> 06:37.005
We tried to turn it around.

06:37.048 --> 06:38.876
Yeah, she pushed it through,
though, but the head

06:38.920 --> 06:40.530
got caught up,

06:40.574 --> 06:43.707
squished like an avocado.

06:43.751 --> 06:45.535
Baby's fine now,
but it's got a...

06:45.579 --> 06:49.060
big ol' dent.

06:49.104 --> 06:50.279
Kinda looks like the baby's got

06:50.322 --> 06:52.455
a little ashtray
on its forehead.

06:52.499 --> 06:54.718
- Brad, just...
- Well, what?

06:54.762 --> 06:57.678
You know Morgan.
I thought you'd want to -- Oh!

07:00.115 --> 07:01.812
You sure you don't want
a bigger one of those?

07:01.856 --> 07:03.771
It's for Engels here.

07:03.814 --> 07:07.731
Keeps parking the patrol car
behind Sammy's to catnap.

07:07.775 --> 07:10.647
I told you -- I'm not napping.
I'm meditating.

07:10.691 --> 07:13.215
Anyway, I was telling your
daughter about Morgan's kid

07:13.258 --> 07:15.260
and how it looks like she's got
a little baby ashtray

07:15.304 --> 07:16.697
- on her face.
- That's great.

07:16.740 --> 07:18.438
- Baby ashtray face.
- Perfect, Brad.

07:18.481 --> 07:19.917
Right?

07:19.961 --> 07:21.919
What?

07:25.532 --> 07:27.969
Listen. Um...

07:28.578 --> 07:30.885
...your mother's cooking dinner
this Thursday.

07:30.928 --> 07:34.279
Be -- Be nice to see you there.

07:34.323 --> 07:36.064
Yeah.

07:38.370 --> 07:40.460
Well, he's always
welcome at the house.

07:40.503 --> 07:41.722
You know that.

07:41.765 --> 07:43.332
Yeah, I know.

07:44.899 --> 07:47.858
Honey, I just want you
to be happy.

07:49.251 --> 07:50.774
We're fine.

07:52.123 --> 07:54.256
Okay.

07:55.823 --> 07:57.041
Hey.

07:59.130 --> 08:01.611
Bye, Dad.

08:07.269 --> 08:09.140
So, uh...

08:09.184 --> 08:11.534
how about one for the deputy?

08:11.578 --> 08:13.710
No? Okay.

08:16.626 --> 08:19.194
Bye, Officers.

09:11.551 --> 09:12.639
You're home late.

09:12.682 --> 09:14.684
Yeah.

09:14.728 --> 09:16.556
Got caught up at Flynn's.

09:17.252 --> 09:20.081
Sal needed a lift again.

09:20.124 --> 09:22.779
Marlene read him the riot act
when you dropped him off?

09:23.954 --> 09:25.956
I did not stick around
to hear that.

09:32.006 --> 09:35.096
Pork chops were half price,
so I bought extra.

09:35.139 --> 09:37.315
Don't fill up on beer.

09:38.055 --> 09:40.231
What did you say?

09:42.712 --> 09:45.672
Nick.

09:45.715 --> 09:46.803
Mm.

09:46.847 --> 09:48.326
Come on.
I got dinner to make.

09:48.370 --> 09:50.372
Mm.

09:53.244 --> 09:54.985
The pork chops
are gonna be cold.

09:55.029 --> 09:56.596
Oh, yeah?

09:58.554 --> 10:01.165
I love cold pork chops.

10:04.473 --> 10:06.344
Mm.

12:22.350 --> 12:25.222
You guys are pretty close
with this Nick fella, huh?

12:26.876 --> 12:28.269
Were.

12:28.312 --> 12:30.750
Ah.

12:39.802 --> 12:42.152
Three of us...

12:43.675 --> 12:46.330
...we were gonna go
down to Mexico.

12:47.592 --> 12:49.246
Buy us an orange grove.

12:51.596 --> 12:55.949
Sit around, drinking tequila.

12:56.950 --> 13:00.649
Fucking seÃ±oritas while
the greasers picked them for us.

13:05.045 --> 13:08.004
- You know, Bruce...
- Huh?

13:08.048 --> 13:10.137
...if things work out...

13:11.181 --> 13:13.749
...you might be able
to come with.

13:14.794 --> 13:16.273
Yeah.

13:16.317 --> 13:18.319
That'd be, uh...

13:18.972 --> 13:20.538
That'd be real special.

13:22.627 --> 13:23.846
You know, not that it matters --

13:23.890 --> 13:26.240
I mean, the job's a job...

13:27.110 --> 13:29.069
...but, um...

13:30.157 --> 13:31.854
...what happened?

13:31.898 --> 13:34.814
Well, you know
what they say about plans.

13:34.857 --> 13:36.467
Yeah.

13:38.730 --> 13:40.820
Shit happens.

13:49.480 --> 13:50.742
Forchet?

13:54.398 --> 13:56.270
Good to put a face to the voice.

14:02.319 --> 14:03.538
You get it?

14:04.191 --> 14:05.453
About that.

14:05.496 --> 14:07.629
Yeah,
the man you're looking for,

14:07.672 --> 14:09.413
he isn't the easiest fella
to find.

14:13.374 --> 14:15.202
You get my address?

14:15.245 --> 14:18.945
More or less.
I got anaddress.

14:18.988 --> 14:21.208
But, uh... thing is,

14:21.251 --> 14:24.951
with travel expenses,

14:24.994 --> 14:27.692
2 grand's just not gonna cut it.

14:28.432 --> 14:30.739
We had a deal.

14:30.782 --> 14:33.133
That wasthe deal.

14:35.135 --> 14:37.615
I'm gonna need another 2 grand.

14:38.442 --> 14:40.575
Another 2 grand?

14:40.618 --> 14:42.490
Hmm.

14:43.143 --> 14:47.190
See, a man in prison

14:47.234 --> 14:50.193
pays you to find another man...

14:51.803 --> 14:53.718
...4 grand just feels right.

14:55.590 --> 14:59.507
I think I'm well within
my bounds to renegotiate.

15:00.987 --> 15:03.206
I don't got it.

15:06.818 --> 15:08.603
Well...

15:08.646 --> 15:11.388
you look like a resourceful man.

15:12.433 --> 15:13.477
I'll wait.

15:24.662 --> 15:27.274
That's $2,000.

15:29.580 --> 15:31.756
You take it.

15:31.800 --> 15:34.194
You give me that address.

15:37.501 --> 15:39.068
Well, I'll tell you what.

15:39.112 --> 15:41.244
I'm-a cut you a deal, alright?

15:41.288 --> 15:43.290
Aaaahhh!

15:43.333 --> 15:44.987
Motherfucker!

15:45.031 --> 15:46.467
We made a deal.

15:46.510 --> 15:48.773
Fuck!

15:48.817 --> 15:51.341
Give me the address.

15:51.385 --> 15:53.169
Give me it.

15:56.912 --> 15:58.000
Here.

15:58.044 --> 16:01.438
Let go. Ow.

16:02.004 --> 16:03.527
Aah, aah!

16:10.012 --> 16:13.189
Shit.

16:44.873 --> 16:46.222
Where to?

16:46.266 --> 16:48.224
Head toward 61.

17:19.733 --> 17:21.779
Fucking Marlene, man.

17:21.823 --> 17:22.911
What's that?

17:22.954 --> 17:24.739
Tuna.
That's what that is.

17:24.781 --> 17:28.176
- Yeah?
- Yeah, every damn day, man.

17:28.221 --> 17:30.179
I ask for something different,
what does she give me? Tuna.

17:30.223 --> 17:31.833
It's like
she's fucking with me, man.

17:31.876 --> 17:35.097
Like, Mexican tuna,
Japanese tuna...

17:35.141 --> 17:36.359
American tuna.
I don't know, man.

17:36.403 --> 17:37.708
- Hey, Sal!
- Yeah?

17:37.752 --> 17:39.275
I got a shift open this weekend.

17:39.319 --> 17:40.450
Are you interested?

17:41.930 --> 17:44.019
No, man. Can't do it. Working
on Jordan's cabin again.

17:44.063 --> 17:46.239
- We got rained out.
- Right, right, yeah.

17:46.282 --> 17:48.110
Building Noah's ark, right?
Mm-hmm.

17:48.154 --> 17:49.416
Enjoy that hunting trip.

17:49.459 --> 17:53.072
Oh, no. No, that's just work.
I swear.

17:53.115 --> 17:54.595
Alright.

17:54.638 --> 17:57.032
Don't be coming next week
begging for a shift

17:57.076 --> 17:59.991
'cause you got rained out.
You understand me?

18:01.732 --> 18:03.647
Yeah, boss.

18:04.866 --> 18:06.476
You can take that shift
if you want, man.

18:06.520 --> 18:09.218
I can work on the cabin myself.
Make it 50/50.

18:09.262 --> 18:10.741
No, man.

18:10.785 --> 18:13.266
Five days a week in this place
is enough for me.

18:13.309 --> 18:15.964
Besides, I want to go hunting.

18:16.007 --> 18:17.618
Hey, man, that reminds me.

18:17.661 --> 18:20.142
- John asked if he could come.
- What'd you tell him?

18:20.186 --> 18:21.535
No, I told him to fuck off, man.

18:21.578 --> 18:22.753
There's not enough room
in the truck.

18:22.797 --> 18:24.015
- Seriously?
- Yeah. If we go hunting,

18:24.059 --> 18:25.408
I don't want to deal with him.

18:25.452 --> 18:26.627
Did you tell him about your gun?

18:26.670 --> 18:28.542
- No.
- Why not?

18:28.585 --> 18:30.326
I owe him money, man.

18:55.525 --> 18:57.962
Frank, do you copy?

19:00.487 --> 19:02.271
Go ahead, Brad.

19:02.315 --> 19:03.620
Hey, I'm taking off.

19:03.664 --> 19:05.448
Garrett's on,
so I'll see you tomorrow.

19:05.492 --> 19:08.364
Copy that.
See you tomorrow.

20:19.740 --> 20:21.611
You make sure
Sal pays you back some

20:21.655 --> 20:23.483
when you get paid for this job.

20:24.571 --> 20:26.268
I will.

20:36.452 --> 20:38.106
What?

20:39.281 --> 20:41.370
You.

20:41.414 --> 20:44.373
Sometimes I think your mind's
a million miles away.

20:52.903 --> 20:54.340
You sure
you're gonna be alright,

20:54.383 --> 20:56.255
me being gone all weekend?

20:56.298 --> 20:57.778
Yeah, I'll be fine.

20:57.821 --> 20:59.693
I promise.

20:59.736 --> 21:02.565
Marlene might come over later,
maybe watch a movie...

21:02.609 --> 21:04.611
if she gets someone
to watch the kids.

21:04.654 --> 21:08.049
You got, um...
Jordan's number, right?

21:08.092 --> 21:10.704
- If you need to get in touch?
- I've got it taken care of.

21:10.747 --> 21:13.141
I will be fine.

21:13.184 --> 21:14.969
Go. Have fun.

21:28.809 --> 21:30.463
Something for the way up.

21:30.506 --> 21:32.421
Thanks, baby.

21:32.465 --> 21:34.162
You got enough food?

21:34.205 --> 21:36.033
Just what's in the cooler.

21:36.077 --> 21:38.993
Well, if you get some time,
bring them back full.

21:39.036 --> 21:40.821
Alright.

21:40.864 --> 21:44.433
I better go get Sal before
Marlene locks him in the house.

21:44.477 --> 21:46.000
Alright, love you.

21:46.043 --> 21:47.915
You too.

22:26.345 --> 22:28.521
You be back here by Sunday,

22:28.564 --> 22:31.567
- or I won't be.
- Yep. Yeah, yeah.

22:31.611 --> 22:33.656
Make sure you pay
attention when you're working.

22:33.700 --> 22:35.658
You can't fix chairs
if you're missing a finger.

22:35.702 --> 22:37.660
I know. I'm gonna try not to
poke an eye out either.

22:37.704 --> 22:39.227
Hey, you look at me.

22:39.270 --> 22:42.317
You're gonna be super-cool
to your mom, right?

22:42.361 --> 22:44.232
That's right. You help her out,
whatever she needs.

22:44.275 --> 22:47.148
And you. You're just --
You're perfect.

22:47.844 --> 22:49.933
- Yeah, you're alright.
- Mm.

22:49.977 --> 22:51.587
Feed her this time.

22:51.631 --> 22:54.155
Yeah, I'll make sure to do that.

22:54.198 --> 22:56.331
Okay. Alright, bye!

22:56.375 --> 22:58.768
Love you!
See you Sunday!

22:58.812 --> 23:01.684
Make sure he stays
out of trouble, Nick.

23:01.728 --> 23:03.686
- Will do.
- Bye.

23:14.175 --> 23:15.698
Oh, let's get the fuck
out of here.

23:15.742 --> 23:18.875
I don't know
how you guys do it, man.

23:18.919 --> 23:20.137
Hard liquor.

23:46.120 --> 23:48.122
Unh-unh.

23:48.165 --> 23:50.864
- We don't serve your kind here.
- Oh, yeah? What's that?

23:50.907 --> 23:53.344
- Smart, handsome men?
- JORDAN:

23:54.520 --> 23:56.173
You got the "men" part right.

23:56.217 --> 23:58.872
- How's it going, buddy?
- How's my cabin coming?

23:58.915 --> 24:01.701
I don't know. I guess we'll
see it when we get up there.

24:02.963 --> 24:04.355
How's it hanging, Sal?

24:04.399 --> 24:06.096
South.

24:06.140 --> 24:08.403
As always, man. Just don't
get up like it used to.

24:08.447 --> 24:10.449
Yeah, I hear you.

24:10.492 --> 24:11.537
What are you ladies drinking?

24:11.580 --> 24:13.713
Oh, anything cold.

24:17.673 --> 24:18.631
On the house.

24:18.674 --> 24:20.110
Hear, hear.

24:20.154 --> 24:22.069
Appreciate it.

24:22.896 --> 24:24.419
How Tara doing?

24:24.463 --> 24:27.814
Yeah, she's --
she's doing alright.

24:27.857 --> 24:29.206
Keeping busy.

24:29.250 --> 24:31.948
- How you doing?
- I'm alright.

24:31.992 --> 24:34.777
You still got
a phone back there?

24:34.821 --> 24:36.823
Yeah, come on back.

24:40.522 --> 24:42.785
Tell Tara I said "hello."

24:42.829 --> 24:44.831
Will do.

25:06.330 --> 25:08.507
Uh, hey, babe.

25:08.550 --> 25:11.945
It's me. We just, uh --
just got to Jordan's.

25:11.988 --> 25:14.425
We're about to head out
to the cabin in a little bit.

25:14.469 --> 25:16.297
Not sure where you are.
I --

25:16.340 --> 25:18.429
- Nick.
- Tara?

25:18.473 --> 25:20.606
Hey, sorry.
I was in the shower.

25:20.649 --> 25:22.085
I heard the machine cut on.

25:22.129 --> 25:23.826
It's alright.

25:23.870 --> 25:25.741
Yeah, we just made it out here
a little bit ago.

25:25.785 --> 25:27.787
Just sitting at Jordan's
having a couple.

25:27.830 --> 25:29.615
Oh.

25:29.658 --> 25:31.225
Having a couple.

25:32.835 --> 25:34.750
You be careful in the dark.

25:34.794 --> 25:36.622
Especially on those roads.

25:36.665 --> 25:38.188
I will.

25:38.232 --> 25:40.277
You eat dinner yet?

25:40.321 --> 25:41.931
Yeah.

25:41.975 --> 25:44.107
Finished the quiche.

25:44.151 --> 25:45.413
Oh, um...

25:45.456 --> 25:47.023
Jordan says "hi."

25:47.067 --> 25:49.373
That's sweet.
You tell him I said "hi" back.

25:49.417 --> 25:52.376
Yeah, I will.

25:52.420 --> 25:53.421
What was that?

25:53.464 --> 25:56.206
Oh, I'm making a pie.

25:56.816 --> 25:58.121
Okay.

25:58.165 --> 26:00.471
In case Marlene comes by.

26:00.515 --> 26:04.040
Speak of the devil.

26:05.172 --> 26:07.174
I gotta go.

26:07.217 --> 26:09.002
Alright.

26:09.045 --> 26:11.221
- I love you.
- Yeah, I love you, too.

26:11.265 --> 26:13.659
I'm coming!

26:13.702 --> 26:16.749
Hold on a goddamn moment,
Marlene.

26:22.929 --> 26:24.408
Hey, man, she left you yet?

26:26.367 --> 26:28.935
You tell her I said "hello"?

26:28.978 --> 26:30.371
Yep.

26:30.414 --> 26:32.329
She said "hi" back.

26:32.373 --> 26:34.288
You tell her I said "hi"?

26:34.331 --> 26:36.333
Hell no.

28:36.497 --> 28:39.108
What?

28:39.152 --> 28:42.895
Hey, man, you'd think I wouldn't
have to ask. You'd just tell me.

28:43.591 --> 28:46.072
This shit, man?

28:46.115 --> 28:48.204
That's a big motherfucker, man.
Looks like it hurt.

28:48.248 --> 28:51.425
Big-ass scar.

28:51.468 --> 28:52.818
Fell down.

28:52.861 --> 28:56.038
Fuck you, man.

28:56.082 --> 28:57.648
Yeah.

28:57.692 --> 29:01.348
Hey, I'm serious, though, man.

29:07.223 --> 29:10.618
I was just hanging out with
the wrong guys for a while.

29:11.793 --> 29:14.578
We were sort of like a...

29:14.622 --> 29:17.581
I don't know what you call it.

29:18.365 --> 29:21.890
Didn't add up to anything good,
that's for sure.

29:24.675 --> 29:26.852
The fuck kind of answer
is that, man?

29:30.377 --> 29:32.248
My dad and Jordan
went back quite a ways,

29:32.292 --> 29:35.164
and he's the one
that introduced me to Junior.

29:35.208 --> 29:38.907
I figured it was better to,
you know...

29:38.951 --> 29:42.650
start new somewhere
where I knew a couple people.

29:43.390 --> 29:45.827
Then I met Tara.

29:45.871 --> 29:47.786
That was it.
That sealed the deal.

29:54.880 --> 29:57.578
You married right
with that one, man.

29:58.622 --> 30:00.189
I mean, at least
your father-in-law

30:00.233 --> 30:01.756
can get you out of tickets.

30:01.800 --> 30:04.193
Mine just kicks me in the teeth.

30:04.237 --> 30:07.283
Yeah, well, we got something
in common on that one.

30:07.327 --> 30:09.982
- Want one?
- Yeah.

30:19.600 --> 30:21.558
I got one, too, you know?

30:21.602 --> 30:23.473
What's that?

30:24.692 --> 30:27.173
Check that out.
See that right there?

30:27.216 --> 30:28.783
Oh, shit.
Where'd you pick that up?

30:28.827 --> 30:31.090
- Marlene.
- Marlene?

30:31.133 --> 30:35.181
Actually,
that was her ex-husband.

30:35.224 --> 30:38.010
I mean, technically, it was
her husband at the time.

30:38.053 --> 30:40.055
Wait.
So you broke up a marriage?

30:40.099 --> 30:41.665
No, no, no.
Wait a minute.

30:41.709 --> 30:44.103
Wasn't like that, man.

30:44.146 --> 30:47.062
She had one foot
out of the door already.

30:47.106 --> 30:48.890
When she came
in the upholstery store,

30:48.934 --> 30:52.024
asked to have her recliner done,

30:52.067 --> 30:54.591
she was just radiating
that energy she has, man.

30:54.635 --> 30:57.856
I was done, man. Took one look
at her. That was it.

30:58.900 --> 31:00.336
Of course,
now that I think about it,

31:00.380 --> 31:02.121
getting her pregnant
before she was divorced

31:02.164 --> 31:03.949
probably sped some things up
a little bit, but...

31:05.907 --> 31:07.909
He didn't take too kindly
to that, and he came in

31:07.953 --> 31:10.607
and hit me in the head
with a tire iron one day.

31:11.391 --> 31:13.915
Yeah, yeah.
I was out for 20 minutes.

31:13.959 --> 31:15.917
Woke up.
About 15 stitches and...

31:15.961 --> 31:18.354
- No shit.
- I don't really remember much,

